<stack-static>
    <statement><div><p>Given the column vectors <m>\mathbf{a} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -3 \end{array}\right]}</m> and <m>\mathbf{b} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -1 \end{array}\right]}</m>, find the following:</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <div><m> \mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} = </m> <fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/>  </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        <div><m> {2}\mathbf{a} - {2}\mathbf{b} = </m> <fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/>  </div>
    </li>
</ol></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p><alert>Part (a)</alert></p>
<p>To add column vectors, we add the corresponding components (top with top, bottom with bottom):</p>
<me> 
\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -3 \end{array}\right]} + {\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -1 \end{array}\right]} 
= \begin{pmatrix} {-5} + ({-5}) \\ {-3} + ({-1}) \end{pmatrix} 
= {\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -4 \end{array}\right]} 
</me>

<p><alert>Part (b)</alert></p>
<p>First, we multiply each vector by its scalar:</p>
<me> {2}\mathbf{a} = {2}{\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -3 \end{array}\right]} = \begin{pmatrix} {2} \times {-5} \\ {2} \times {-3} \end{pmatrix} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -6 \end{array}\right]} </me>
<me> {2}\mathbf{b} = {2}{\left[\begin{array}{c} -5 \\ -1 \end{array}\right]} = \begin{pmatrix} {2} \times {-5} \\ {2} \times {-1} \end{pmatrix} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -2 \end{array}\right]} </me>

<p>Then we subtract the results:</p>
<me> 
{2}\mathbf{a} - {2}\mathbf{b} = {\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -6 \end{array}\right]} - {\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -2 \end{array}\right]} 
= \begin{pmatrix} {-10} - ({-10}) \\ {-6} - ({-2}) \end{pmatrix} 
= {\left[\begin{array}{c} 0 \\ -4 \end{array}\right]} 
</me></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left[\begin{array}{c} -10 \\ -4 \end{array}\right]</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>\left[\begin{array}{c} 0 \\ -4 \end{array}\right]</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>